HEADWORD: Synocil
<hw>Syn"o*cil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>syn-</ets> + <ets>cil</ets>ium.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
sense organ found in certain sponges. It consists of several filaments,
each of which arises from a single cell.</def>⟦br⟧
